Class Projectile

  • java.lang.Object
    • animation.Projectile

  • public class Projectile
extends java.lang.Object
    Purpose: Projectile for usage with tower Entity types. 
     Allows for constructing various projectiles, unique to the various tower types.
 Provides the methods for their animations, transitioning, and detecting when they 
 hit their target, and how to update said information.
    Author:
    Hualiang Qin, Louis Galluzzi, Clinton Kral, John Stockey

      • Projectile

        public Projectile(javafx.scene.layout.StackPane stage,
                  int y,
                  double speed,
                  java.lang.String mode,
                  java.lang.String action,
                  int count,
                  int attack,
                  int x,
                  Entity target,
                  int hits)
        Purpose: Contructor for creating a new projectile.
        Parameters:
        stage - A StackPane for showing the animation.
        y - An int of the row position.
        speed - A double for the speed of the projectile.
        mode - A String of the mode to animate in.
        action - A String of the animation to build and show.
        count - An int of the number of frames for the animation.
        attack - An int of the attack amount.
        x - An int of the x position.
        target - An Entity of the target.
        hits - An int of the number of hits to make.
